theorem Topology.closure_eq_univ_iff_interior_compl_empty {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) ↔ interior (Aᶜ) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro h_dense
    exact
      Topology.interior_compl_eq_empty_of_dense (X := X) (A := A) h_dense
  · intro h_int_empty
    -- We first show that `(closure A)ᶜ` is empty.
    have h_subset : ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ (∅ : Set X) := by
      -- `(closure A)ᶜ` is open and contained in `Aᶜ`,
      -- hence contained in `interior (Aᶜ) = ∅`.
      have h_open : IsOpen ((closure A)ᶜ) :=
        isClosed_closure.isOpen_compl
      have h_sub : ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ (Aᶜ) := by
        intro x hx
        by_contra hA
        have : (x : X) ∈ closure A := subset_closure hA
        exact (hx this).elim
      have h_into : ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ interior (Aᶜ) :=
        interior_maximal h_sub h_open
      simpa [h_int_empty] using h_into
    have h_compl_empty : ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) := by
      exact Set.Subset.antisymm h_subset (Set.empty_subset _)
    -- Taking complements, we obtain the desired equality.
    have h_closure_univ : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      apply Set.Subset.antisymm
      · exact Set.Subset_univ _
      · intro x _
        by_contra hx
        have : (x : X) ∈ ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) := hx
        simpa [h_compl_empty] using this
    simpa using h_closure_univ

theorem Topology.interior_union_interior_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (interior A ∪ interior B) = interior A ∪ interior B := by
  have h_open : IsOpen (interior A ∪ interior B) :=
    (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior A)).union isOpen_interior
  simpa using h_open.interior_eq
